msg: (read_entry): When reading the depth field from the this_dir entry,
don't dereference the return value of read_val() unconditionally.
It may be NULL on an empty (e.g. default) entry line.
Spotted while appending new fields to the this_dir entry for tree
conflicts, where this caused a segfault.
who also corrected my initially proposed fix which was backwards, literally
